).

Philautus maia

is distinguished from all other Sri Lankan species of 

Philautus

by the following combination of characters: (
1
) tympanum discernible; (
2
) angle of snout in dorsal aspect ~ 
100
º; (
3
) supratympanic fold distinct; (
4
) canthal edges sharp; (
5
) lingual papilla absent; (
6
) supernumerary tubercles present on fingers but absent on toes; (
7
) tarsal tubercle absent; (
8
) webbing up to or beyond second and third toes (

Fig. 
6

D); (
9
) posterior surface of thigh with a dark­brown reticulated pattern.
